///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Software for computing persistence of input point cloud 
//
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

	To compile, you need to have the following libraries installed:

		* Boost (www.boost.org) 
		* ANN (http://www.cs.umd.edu/~mount/ANN/) 
		* OpenCV (http://opencv.org/) 

	Packages are available for Ubuntu Linux.

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Compilation
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

After Boost and ANN have been installed,
	1. Open a terminal
	2. Go to folder location src
	3. Run: ./build.sh
	4. The binary file named 'pers' should be created
	5. For instructions on how to use it, please go to SOFTWARE_README
A pre-built binary for Ubuntu has been included in the folder named 'pre-built'
 
